rComments: His lectures are completely based off the readings. The readings are supposed to enhance the course not teach it. He goes on a lot of tangents, and gives unclear instructions for assignments. He is very knowledgeable about this topic and uses relevant examples. However, the lecture's move really fast, and all the material is already in the readings

Really interesting lectures. Really smart guy, intimidating, but great person to get to know. Expects you to work, but nothing that's not acheivable. Course content is interesting and he makes it interesting. If you have his class it's important to go to lectures.

Lectures were very engaging and relatable. He doesn't post slides or lecture notes, so you need to come to class. More clarification for assignments and exams would be useful, especially since they were marked quite hard. He expects you to write well and exams are essay form. He is helpful if you go to his office hours and replies to emails quickly
